{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Metal 2 provides powerful and specialized support for Virtual Reality (VR) rendering and external GPUs. Get details about adopting these emerging technologies within your Metal 2-based apps and games on macOS High Sierra. Walk through integrating Metal 2 with the SteamVR SDK and learn about efficiently rendering to a VR headset. Understand how external GPUs take macOS graphics to a whole new level and see how to prepare your apps to take advantage of their full potential."}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"title":"VR with Metal 2","roleHeading":"WWDC17","role":"sampleCode"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-603-VR-with-Metal-2"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Related-Sessions","level":2,"text":"Related Sessions"},{"type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-611-Metal-for-VR","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-601-Introducing-Metal-2"],"style":"list"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/603\/","overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-603-vr-with-metal-2"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg"}],"role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 9, Swift 4.0, iOS 11, macOS 10.13 (High Sierra), tvOS 11, watchOS 4."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Core NFC"},{"type":"text","text":" and more."}],"type":"topic","title":"WWDC17","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"title":"WWDC Notes"},"https://nonstrict.eu/wwdcindex/wwdc2017/603/":{"identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/603\/","url":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2017\/603\/","checksum":null,"type":"download"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"title":"Learn More…","type":"link"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC18-611-Metal-for-VR":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc18-611-metal-for-vr","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"On macOS, Metal 2 adds specialized support for virtual reality (VR) rendering and external GPUs. Learn about new features and optimizations to take advantage of these technologies within your Metal 2-based apps and games. Understand best practices for scheduling workloads across multiple GPUs and techniques for frame pacing while multi-threading.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"Metal for VR","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC18-611-Metal-for-VR"},"WWDC17.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC17.jpeg","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image"},"WWDC17-Icon.png":{"identifier":"WWDC17-Icon.png","alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-Icon.png"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC17-601-Introducing-Metal-2":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc17-601-introducing-metal-2","type":"topic","title":"Introducing Metal 2","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC17-601-Introducing-Metal-2","role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Metal 2 provides near-direct access to the graphics processor (GPU), enabling your apps and games to realize their full graphics and compute potential. Dive into the breakthrough features of Metal 2 that empower the GPU to take control over key aspects of the rendering pipeline. Check out how Metal 2 enables essential tasks to be specified on-the-fly by the GPU, opening up new efficiencies for advanced rendering.","type":"text"}]}}}